6595d5e0e40533319c0188c2.housing_experience: Over the past five years I’ve stayed in the same townhouse in Chinatown Los Angeles. I haven’t moved, but my rent has gradually risen from about $900 per month five years ago to $1,500 today. Each year when the lease renewed, the rent increase was a reminder of L.A.’s tight housing market, but I’ve chosen to stay put for the stability it provides and to keep my commute to school and work manageable.
